f=Engineering/mia/custom/frontend-verification/SKILL.md · in=frontend-verification mia proves actually works, closing loop department built close ("agents say done; browsers tell truth"). Two complementary tools: **Agentation** (MCP) turns human annotations click element, draw area, freeze state structured, component-aware context (CSS selectors, React tree, computed styles) mia knows exactly what change where; **quinn's browser-verification** (Reticle edit-gate, Playwright release-gate) proves change rendered real state real data. Agentation input; quinn's gate proof. · p=Frontend "done" often false: component looks built shows mock data, button wired nothing, state never updates. Agentation removes ambiguity *what fix* (precise, component-aware feedback instead "the thing off"); quinn's browser-verification removes doubt *whether it's fixed* (real rendering, claim). Together they make frontend "done" mean done. · wu=Triggers: "the wrong/off," feedback act on, "did render," "verify frontend," frontend diff review (edit gate), any user-facing release (release gate), mock-data/placeholder suspicion. · st:/ Protocol=`FEEDBACK IN (Agentation MCP — when connected) \· Human annotates the running UI (click/area/state-freeze) → structured context: \· CSS selector \· React component tree \· computed styles \· the ask \· -> mia acts on precise context, not a vague description → change with a known file:line target \· -> mia can acknowledge / resolve-with-summary / dismiss-with-reason (Agentation's two-way loop)` · in=**Agentation precise input.** feedback arrives, use Agentation's structured context (selector, component tree, computed styles) rather guessing what "make cleaner" means. component-aware target means change lands right `file:line` first time antidote vague-feedback-vague-fix loop. **Use two-way loop honestly.** Acknowledge starting, resolve real summary what changed, dismiss genuine reason state timestamped. Don't mark resolved what isn't (the Agentation-era version "agents say done"). **quinn's edit gate frontend diff.** change verified running app: element renders, state real (mock/fixture data DOM integrity block dev §0), expected network calls fire, change traces source. mia produces evidence review. **quinn's release gate user flows.** Critical flows pass real browser (Playwright) before release E-tier quinn's matrix, surfaces mia owns. **Degrade loudly without connectors.** Agentation feedback handled description, labeled less precise. Reticle/Playwright verification labeled manual checklist. gate never silently shrinks (quinn's rule, inherited). **Verification charter-bound.** Browser runs external tool calls: plan-locked (Rail 1), sandboxed, egress-allowlisted (Rail 2); test data synthetic, never production. · of=`## Frontend Verification: [change/release] \· Feedback input: [Agentation context ref: selector/component/styles / description-only, labeled] \· Edit gate (Reticle): [element ✓ \· real data ✓ / mock found → integrity block \· network ✓ \· file:line] \· Release gate (Playwright): [critical flows PASS/FAIL] \· Loop state: [acknowledged/resolved-with-summary/dismissed-with-reason]` · pr=**Agentation precise input; quinn's gate proof** input verification, complementary same., **Component-aware feedback right file:line first time** vague-fix loop., **The two-way loop used honestly** resolved means resolved, dismissed carries reason., **Mock data DOM integrity block** cosmetic note (dev §0)., **Degrade loudly** missing tools shrink capability, never silently shrink gate., **Charter-bound runs** plan-locked, sandboxed, synthetic data. · f=Agentation connector act written feedback, labeled less precise; recommend adoption (plan §5) operator., Reticle/Playwright manual verification checklist, labeled "unverified tooling"; release E-tier reports UNMET., Feedback ambiguous even Agentation ask specific annotation rather guess; precise tooling deserves precise ask. · b:with Other Skills=**quinn/browser-verification**: OWNS gates (Reticle edit, Playwright release); skill produces evidence adds Agentation feedback-input side. mia doesn't re-implement quinn's gate; feeds it., **ui-accessibility-standards design-tokens** (siblings): what's verified accessible, consistent, token-based real data., **raj**: verification catches frontend consuming raj's API wrong (mock data real call be)., **dev integrity**: mock-data-rendering frontend instance agent-authored-code integrity block.